		<body>
		<pb n="1"/>
		
		<p rend="align(center)"><placeName>St Thomas</placeName> <date>9 Sep 1846</date></p>
		<p>My <addressee>Dr Mr. Leeser</addressee></p>
		  <p rend="indent(3)">A great many of our children<lb/> have been neglected since I was forced from the Sunday<lb/> School&#44; the parents declining to send them under the<lb/> existing regulations of the present <del>school</del>.  I have<lb/> altho&#39; urged&#44; declined forming one for these who do not<lb/> receive the benefits&#44; as I did not wish to come into<lb/> contact with the opposite party&#44; finding however that the<lb/> children were really suffering&#44; &amp; at the particular<lb/> solicitation of one of our most Respectable &amp; influential<lb/> members &#40;who unhappily &#40;was in <placeName>Europe</placeName> when the differences<lb/> took place&#41; having a large number of children&#44; that really<lb/> require the advantage of Religious instruction&#8211;have<lb/> promised him to re&#45;commence &amp; intend doing so as soon as<lb/> I shall receive from you the following books which I<lb/> require.</p>
		  <p rend="indent(1)">36 Pyher[&#63;] &amp; catechisms</p>
		  <p rend="indent(1)">36 cahiev[&#63;]&#8211;24 Bible questions&#44; by <persName>Miss Peixotto</persName> &amp;</p>
		  <p rend="indent(1)">12 of your Catechisms&#59; I beg that you will</p>
		

		<pb n="2"/>
		
		<p>send them with all haste.  Wishing you many happy<lb/> holy days I am my Dr Sir Yours Truly</p>
		  <p rend="indent(8)"><persName role="author">A Wolff</persName></p>
		

		<pb n="3"/>
		
		<p>7</p>
		<p><addressee>Revd. Mr Leeser</addressee></p>
		  <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
		</body>
